1.title: Esther's Voice
1.plot: Censorship is the suppression of speech or other public communication which may be considered objectionable, harmful, sensitive, or inconvenient. This uncovers the censorship of domestic abuse and speaking candidly about it in order to break the stigma surrounding this issue. Changing the conversation surrounding domestic abuse requires many voices to speak up. It is a global epidemic. Join us as we look through real eyes and realize you are not alone. Speak up. Be heard.
